page.title: 09Square 8
page.content:
This square has three dominant land covers. The principle land cover is{ {Enclosed rough grazing,}with{Deciduous {woodland}and{Crops}as the minor land covers. There are only two houses in this square, which are occupied by estate workers, therefore they are only rented accomodation. This square has a regular bus service, unlike most of the other squares, which takes people to Chester which is the major city in the region.
{Attitudes { }The inhabitants of this square work for the westminster estate, and have their accomodation provided. They live a quiet life, and do not welcome modern changes.
